==English==

===Noun===
'''double double''' or '''double-double'''

#(''Canadian'') {{slang}} [[Coffee]] with the equivalent of two creamers and two packets of sugar.
#{{basketball}} The achievement of a two-digit number of any two of points scored, assists, rebounds, blocks, or steals in a single game.
#: ''The Nimrods' center had 11 assists and 10 blocks tonight for a very unusual double double.''
#{{US}} A double cheeseburger with cheese on each burger (i.e., double cheese).

